name: drive
title: Drive API
description: Manages files in Drive including uploading, downloading, searching, detecting changes, and updating sharing permissions.

enum.name: json
enum.desc: Responses with Content-Type of application/json

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

schemas.name: ChildList
schemas.desc: A list of children of a file.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of children. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#childList.

fields.name: nextLink
fields.desc: A link to the next page of children.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of children. This will be absent if the end of the children list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

schemas.name: ParentList
schemas.desc: A list of a file's parents.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of parents.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#parentList.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "drive#startPageToken".

fields.name: startPageToken
fields.desc: The starting page token for listing changes.

schemas.name: ChildReference
schemas.desc: A reference to a folder's child.

fields.name: childLink
fields.desc: A link to the child.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the child.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#childReference.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this reference.

schemas.name: About
schemas.desc: An item with user information and settings.

fields.name: additionalRoleInfo
fields.desc: Information about supported additional roles per file type. The most specific type takes precedence.

fields.name: roleSets
fields.desc: The supported additional roles per primary role.

fields.name: additionalRoles
fields.desc: The supported additional roles with the primary role.

fields.name: primaryRole
fields.desc: A primary permission role.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The content type that this additional role info applies to.

fields.name: quotaBytesTotal
fields.desc: The total number of quota bytes.

fields.name: rootFolderId
fields.desc: The id of the root folder.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this item.

fields.name: quotaBytesByService
fields.desc: The amount of storage quota used by different Google services.

fields.name: bytesUsed
fields.desc: The storage quota bytes used by the service.

fields.name: serviceName
fields.desc: The service's name, e.g. DRIVE, GMAIL, or PHOTOS.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the item.

fields.name: exportFormats
fields.desc: The allowable export formats.

fields.name: source
fields.desc: The content type to convert from.

fields.name: targets
fields.desc: The possible content types to convert to.

fields.name: folderColorPalette
fields.desc: The palette of allowable folder colors as RGB hex strings.

fields.name: importFormats
fields.desc: The allowable import formats.

fields.name: source
fields.desc: The imported file's content type to convert from.

fields.name: targets
fields.desc: The possible content types to convert to.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#about.

fields.name: largestChangeId
fields.desc: The largest change id.

fields.name: maxUploadSizes
fields.desc: List of max upload sizes for each file type. The most specific type takes precedence.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: The max upload size for this type.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The file type.

fields.name: quotaType
fields.desc:
The type of the user's storage quota. Possible values are:  
- LIMITED 
- UNLIMITED

fields.name: remainingChangeIds
fields.desc: The number of remaining change ids, limited to no more than 2500.

fields.name: user
fields.desc: The authenticated user.

fields.name: languageCode
fields.desc: The user's language or locale code, as defined by BCP 47, with some extensions from Unicode's LDML format (http://www.unicode.org/reports/tr35/).

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the current user.

fields.name: permissionId
fields.desc: The current user's ID as visible in the permissions collection.

fields.name: quotaBytesUsed
fields.desc: The number of quota bytes used by Google Drive.

fields.name: quotaBytesUsedInTrash
fields.desc: The number of quota bytes used by trashed items.

fields.name: domainSharingPolicy
fields.desc:
The domain sharing policy for the current user. Possible values are:  
- allowed 
- allowedWithWarning 
- incomingOnly 
- disallowed

fields.name: features
fields.desc: List of additional features enabled on this account.

fields.name: featureName
fields.desc: The name of the feature.

fields.name: featureRate
fields.desc: The request limit rate for this feature, in queries per second.

fields.name: isCurrentAppInstalled
fields.desc: A boolean indicating whether the authenticated app is installed by the authenticated user.

fields.name: quotaBytesUsedAggregate
fields.desc: The number of quota bytes used by all Google apps (Drive, Picasa, etc.).

schemas.name: AppList
schemas.desc: A list of third-party applications which the user has installed or given access to Google Drive.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#appList.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

fields.name: defaultAppIds
fields.desc: List of app IDs that the user has specified to use by default. The list is in reverse-priority order (lowest to highest).

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of apps.

schemas.name: App
schemas.desc: The apps resource provides a list of the apps that a user has installed, with information about each app's supported MIME types, file extensions, and other details.

fields.name: primaryMimeTypes
fields.desc: The list of primary mime types.

fields.name: supportsImport
fields.desc: Whether this app supports importing Google Docs.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#app.

fields.name: longDescription
fields.desc: A long description of the app.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the app.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the app.

fields.name: supportsOfflineCreate
fields.desc: Whether this app supports creating new files when offline.

fields.name: useByDefault
fields.desc: Whether the app is selected as the default handler for the types it supports.

fields.name: authorized
fields.desc: Whether the app is authorized to access data on the user's Drive.

fields.name: createUrl
fields.desc: The url to create a new file with this app.

fields.name: openUrlTemplate
fields.desc: The template url for opening files with this app. The template will contain {ids} and/or {exportIds} to be replaced by the actual file ids. See  Open Files  for the full documentation.

fields.name: productUrl
fields.desc: A link to the product listing for this app.

fields.name: secondaryMimeTypes
fields.desc: The list of secondary mime types.

fields.name: shortDescription
fields.desc: A short description of the app.

fields.name: createInFolderTemplate
fields.desc: The template url to create a new file with this app in a given folder. The template will contain {folderId} to be replaced by the folder to create the new file in.

fields.name: icons
fields.desc: The various icons for the app.

fields.name: category
fields.desc:
Category of the icon. Allowed values are:  
- application - icon for the application 
- document - icon for a file associated with the app 
- documentShared - icon for a shared file associated with the app

fields.name: iconUrl
fields.desc: URL for the icon.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: Size of the icon. Represented as the maximum of the width and height.

fields.name: objectType
fields.desc: The type of object this app creates (e.g. Chart). If empty, the app name should be used instead.

fields.name: primaryFileExtensions
fields.desc: The list of primary file extensions.

fields.name: productId
fields.desc: The ID of the product listing for this app.

fields.name: secondaryFileExtensions
fields.desc: The list of secondary file extensions.

fields.name: supportsCreate
fields.desc: Whether this app supports creating new objects.

fields.name: supportsMultiOpen
fields.desc: Whether this app supports opening more than one file.

fields.name: hasDriveWideScope
fields.desc: Whether the app has drive-wide scope. An app with drive-wide scope can access all files in the user's drive.

fields.name: installed
fields.desc: Whether the app is installed.

schemas.name: Comment
schemas.desc: A comment on a file in Google Drive.

fields.name: status
fields.desc:
The status of this comment. Status can be changed by posting a reply to a comment with the desired status.  
- "open" - The comment is still open. 
- "resolved" - The comment has been resolved by one of its replies.

fields.name: commentId
fields.desc: The ID of the comment.

fields.name: content
fields.desc: The plain text content used to create this comment. This is not HTML safe and should only be used as a starting point to make edits to a comment's content.

fields.name: fileId
fields.desc: The file which this comment is addressing.

fields.name: htmlContent
fields.desc: HTML formatted content for this comment.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this comment.

fields.name: anchor
fields.desc: A region of the document represented as a JSON string. See anchor documentation for details on how to define and interpret anchor properties.

fields.name: fileTitle
fields.desc: The title of the file which this comment is addressing.

fields.name: author
fields.desc: The user who wrote this comment.

fields.name: createdDate
fields.desc: The date when this comment was first created.

fields.name: context
fields.desc: The context of the file which is being commented on.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The MIME type of the context snippet.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: Data representation of the segment of the file being commented on. In the case of a text file for example, this would be the actual text that the comment is about.

fields.name: deleted
fields.desc: Whether this comment has been deleted. If a comment has been deleted the content will be cleared and this will only represent a comment that once existed.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#comment.

fields.name: modifiedDate
fields.desc: The date when this comment or any of its replies were last modified.

fields.name: replies
fields.desc: Replies to this post.

schemas.name: Permission
schemas.desc: A permission for a file.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the permission.

fields.name: photoLink
fields.desc: A link to the profile photo, if available.

fields.name: teamDrivePermissionDetails
fields.desc: Details of whether the Permissions on this Team Drive item are inherited or directly on this item. This is an output-only field which is present only for Team Drive items.

fields.name: inherited
fields.desc: Whether this permission is inherited. This field is always populated. This is an output-only field.

fields.name: inheritedFrom
fields.desc: The ID of the item from which this permission is inherited. This is an output-only field and is only populated for members of the Team Drive.

fields.name: role
fields.desc:
The primary role for this user. While new values may be added in the future, the following are currently possible:  
- organizer 
- reader 
- writer

fields.name: teamDrivePermissionType
fields.desc:
The Team Drive permission type for this user. While new values may be added in future, the following are currently possible:  
- file 
- member

fields.name: additionalRoles
fields.desc: Additional roles for this user. Only commenter is currently possible, though more may be supported in the future.

fields.name: type
fields.desc:
The account type. Allowed values are:  
- user 
- group 
- domain 
- anyone

fields.name: additionalRoles
fields.desc: Additional roles for this user. Only commenter is currently allowed, though more may be supported in the future.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the user this permission refers to, and identical to the permissionId in the About and Files resources. When making a drive.permissions.insert request, exactly one of the id or value fields must be specified unless the permission type is anyone, in which case both id and value are ignored.

fields.name: role
fields.desc:
The primary role for this user. While new values may be supported in the future, the following are currently allowed:  
- organizer 
- owner 
- reader 
- writer

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The email address or domain name for the entity. This is used during inserts and is not populated in responses. When making a drive.permissions.insert request, exactly one of the id or value fields must be specified unless the permission type is anyone, in which case both id and value are ignored.

fields.name: emailAddress
fields.desc: The email address of the user or group this permission refers to. This is an output-only field which is present when the permission type is user or group.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name for this permission.

fields.name: authKey
fields.desc: The authkey parameter required for this permission.

fields.name: domain
fields.desc: The domain name of the entity this permission refers to. This is an output-only field which is present when the permission type is user, group or domain.

fields.name: expirationDate
fields.desc:
The time at which this permission will expire (RFC 3339 date-time). Expiration dates have the following restrictions:  
- They can only be set on user and group permissions 
- The date must be in the future 
- The date cannot be more than a year in the future 
- The date can only be set on drive.permissions.update requests

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#permission.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this permission.

fields.name: withLink
fields.desc: Whether the link is required for this permission.

schemas.name: PermissionId
schemas.desc: An ID for a user or group as seen in Permission items.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The permission ID.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#permissionId.

schemas.name: Property
schemas.desc:
A key-value pair attached to a file that is either public or private to an application.
The following limits apply to file properties:  
- Maximum of 100 properties total per file
- Maximum of 30 private properties per app
- Maximum of 30 public properties
- Maximum of 124 bytes size limit on (key + value) string in UTF-8 encoding for a single property.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The value of this property.

fields.name: visibility
fields.desc: The visibility of this property.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the property.

fields.name: key
fields.desc: The key of this property.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#property.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The link back to this property.

schemas.name: PropertyList
schemas.desc: A collection of properties, key-value pairs that are either public or private to an application.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of properties.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#propertyList.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The link back to this list.

schemas.name: Revision
schemas.desc: A revision of a file.

fields.name: modifiedDate
fields.desc: Last time this revision was modified (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp).

fields.name: publishedOutsideDomain
fields.desc: Whether this revision is published outside the domain. This is only populated and can only be modified for Google Docs.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this revision.

fields.name: downloadUrl
fields.desc: Short term download URL for the file. This will only be populated on files with content stored in Drive.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the revision.

fields.name: fileSize
fields.desc: The size of the revision in bytes. This will only be populated on files with content stored in Drive.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the revision.

fields.name: md5Checksum
fields.desc: An MD5 checksum for the content of this revision. This will only be populated on files with content stored in Drive.

fields.name: originalFilename
fields.desc: The original filename when this revision was created. This will only be populated on files with content stored in Drive.

fields.name: pinned
fields.desc: Whether this revision is pinned to prevent automatic purging. This will only be populated and can only be modified on files with content stored in Drive which are not Google Docs. Revisions can also be pinned when they are created through the drive.files.insert/update/copy by using the pinned query parameter.

fields.name: published
fields.desc: Whether this revision is published. This is only populated and can only be modified for Google Docs.

fields.name: exportLinks
fields.desc: Links for exporting Google Docs to specific formats.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#revision.

fields.name: lastModifyingUser
fields.desc: The last user to modify this revision.

fields.name: lastModifyingUserName
fields.desc: Name of the last user to modify this revision.

fields.name: mimeType
fields.desc: The MIME type of the revision.

fields.name: publishedLink
fields.desc: A link to the published revision.

fields.name: publishAuto
fields.desc: Whether subsequent revisions will be automatically republished. This is only populated and can only be modified for Google Docs.

schemas.name: RevisionList
schemas.desc: A list of revisions of a file.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of revisions. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#revisionList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of revisions. This field will be absent if the end of the revisions list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

schemas.name: ChangeList
schemas.desc: A list of changes for a user.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of changes. This will be absent if the end of the changes list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of changes. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#changeList.

fields.name: largestChangeId
fields.desc: The current largest change ID.

fields.name: newStartPageToken
fields.desc: The starting page token for future changes. This will be present only if the end of the current changes list has been reached.

fields.name: nextLink
fields.desc: A link to the next page of changes.

schemas.name: TeamDrive
schemas.desc: Representation of a Team Drive.

fields.name: capabilities
fields.desc: Capabilities the current user has on this Team Drive.

fields.name: canRemoveChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can remove children from folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canAddChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can add children to folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canDeleteTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether this Team Drive can be deleted by the current user.

fields.name: canDownload
fields.desc: Whether files in this Team Drive can be downloaded by the current user.

fields.name: canListChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can list the children of folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canManageMembers
fields.desc: Whether the current user can add members to this Team Drive or remove them or change their role.

fields.name: canReadRevisions
fields.desc: Whether the current user has read access to the Revisions resource of files in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canRename
fields.desc: Whether files or folders in this Team Drive can be renamed by the current user.

fields.name: canRenameTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether this Team Drive can be renamed by the current user.

fields.name: canComment
fields.desc: Whether the current user can comment on files in this Team Drive.

fields.name: canCopy
fields.desc: Whether files in this Team Drive can be copied by the current user.

fields.name: canEdit
fields.desc: Whether files in this Team Drive can be edited by the current user.

fields.name: canShare
fields.desc: Whether the current user can share files or folders in this Team Drive.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of this Team Drive which is also the ID of the top level folder for this Team Drive.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#teamDrive

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of this Team Drive.

schemas.name: CommentList
schemas.desc: A list of comments on a file in Google Drive.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#commentList.

fields.name: nextLink
fields.desc: A link to the next page of comments.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of comments. This will be absent if the end of the comments list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of comments. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

schemas.name: CommentReplyList
schemas.desc: A list of replies to a comment on a file in Google Drive.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of replies. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#commentReplyList.

fields.name: nextLink
fields.desc: A link to the next page of replies.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of replies. This will be absent if the end of the replies list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

schemas.name: FileList
schemas.desc: A list of files.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of files. If nextPageToken is populated, then this list may be incomplete and an additional page of results should be fetched.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#fileList.

fields.name: nextLink
fields.desc: A link to the next page of files.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of files. This will be absent if the end of the files list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: incompleteSearch
fields.desc: Whether the search process was incomplete. If true, then some search results may be missing, since all documents were not searched. This may occur when searching multiple Team Drives with the "default,allTeamDrives" corpora, but all corpora could not be searched. When this happens, it is suggested that clients narrow their query by choosing a different corpus such as "default" or "teamDrive".

schemas.name: GeneratedIds
schemas.desc: A list of generated IDs which can be provided in insert requests

fields.name: ids
fields.desc: The IDs generated for the requesting user in the specified space.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#generatedIds

fields.name: space
fields.desc: The type of file that can be created with these IDs.

schemas.name: Change
schemas.desc: Representation of a change to a file or Team Drive.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the change.

fields.name: teamDriveId
fields.desc: The ID of the Team Drive associated with this change.

fields.name: modificationDate
fields.desc: The time of this modification.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this change.

fields.name: teamDrive
fields.desc: The updated state of the Team Drive. Present if the type is teamDrive, the user is still a member of the Team Drive, and the Team Drive has not been deleted.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the change. Possible values are file and teamDrive.

fields.name: deleted
fields.desc: Whether the file or Team Drive has been removed from this list of changes, for example by deletion or loss of access.

fields.name: file
fields.desc: The updated state of the file. Present if the type is file and the file has not been removed from this list of changes.

fields.name: fileId
fields.desc: The ID of the file associated with this change.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#change.

schemas.name: File
schemas.desc: The metadata for a file.

fields.name: hasThumbnail
fields.desc: Whether this file has a thumbnail.

fields.name: modifiedByMeDate
fields.desc: Last time this file was modified by the user (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp). Note that setting modifiedDate will also update the modifiedByMe date for the user which set the date.

fields.name: version
fields.desc: A monotonically increasing version number for the file. This reflects every change made to the file on the server, even those not visible to the requesting user.

fields.name: webContentLink
fields.desc: A link for downloading the content of the file in a browser using cookie based authentication. In cases where the content is shared publicly, the content can be downloaded without any credentials.

fields.name: webViewLink
fields.desc: A link only available on public folders for viewing their static web assets (HTML, CSS, JS, etc) via Google Drive's Website Hosting.

fields.name: canComment
fields.desc: Whether the current user can comment on the file. Deprecated: use capabilities/canComment.

fields.name: copyable
fields.desc: Whether the file can be copied by the current user. Deprecated: use capabilities/canCopy.

fields.name: iconLink
fields.desc: A link to the file's icon.

fields.name: lastModifyingUser
fields.desc: The last user to modify this file.

fields.name: lastViewedByMeDate
fields.desc: Last time this file was viewed by the user (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp).

fields.name: description
fields.desc: A short description of the file.

fields.name: headRevisionId
fields.desc: The ID of the file's head revision. This field is only populated for files with content stored in Drive; it is not populated for Google Docs or shortcut files.

fields.name: shared
fields.desc: Whether the file has been shared. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: videoMediaMetadata
fields.desc: Metadata about video media. This will only be present for video types.

fields.name: durationMillis
fields.desc: The duration of the video in milliseconds.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: The height of the video in pixels.

fields.name: width
fields.desc: The width of the video in pixels.

fields.name: alternateLink
fields.desc: A link for opening the file in a relevant Google editor or viewer.

fields.name: embedLink
fields.desc: A link for embedding the file.

fields.name: imageMediaMetadata
fields.desc: Metadata about image media. This will only be present for image types, and its contents will depend on what can be parsed from the image content.

fields.name: cameraModel
fields.desc: The model of the camera used to create the photo.

fields.name: date
fields.desc: The date and time the photo was taken (EXIF format timestamp).

fields.name: exposureMode
fields.desc: The exposure mode used to create the photo.

fields.name: flashUsed
fields.desc: Whether a flash was used to create the photo.

fields.name: focalLength
fields.desc: The focal length used to create the photo, in millimeters.

fields.name: meteringMode
fields.desc: The metering mode used to create the photo.

fields.name: whiteBalance
fields.desc: The white balance mode used to create the photo.

fields.name: aperture
fields.desc: The aperture used to create the photo (f-number).

fields.name: exposureBias
fields.desc: The exposure bias of the photo (APEX value).

fields.name: isoSpeed
fields.desc: The ISO speed used to create the photo.

fields.name: lens
fields.desc: The lens used to create the photo.

fields.name: sensor
fields.desc: The type of sensor used to create the photo.

fields.name: width
fields.desc: The width of the image in pixels.

fields.name: colorSpace
fields.desc: The color space of the photo.

fields.name: maxApertureValue
fields.desc: The smallest f-number of the lens at the focal length used to create the photo (APEX value).

fields.name: rotation
fields.desc: The rotation in clockwise degrees from the image's original orientation.

fields.name: subjectDistance
fields.desc: The distance to the subject of the photo, in meters.

fields.name: cameraMake
fields.desc: The make of the camera used to create the photo.

fields.name: exposureTime
fields.desc: The length of the exposure, in seconds.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: The height of the image in pixels.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: Geographic location information stored in the image.

fields.name: altitude
fields.desc: The altitude stored in the image.

fields.name: latitude
fields.desc: The latitude stored in the image.

fields.name: longitude
fields.desc: The longitude stored in the image.

fields.name: trashingUser
fields.desc: If the file has been explicitly trashed, the user who trashed it. Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: spaces
fields.desc: The list of spaces which contain the file. Supported values are 'drive', 'appDataFolder' and 'photos'.

fields.name: teamDriveId
fields.desc: ID of the Team Drive the file resides in.

fields.name: appDataContents
fields.desc: Whether this file is in the Application Data folder.

fields.name: thumbnail
fields.desc: A thumbnail for the file. This will only be used if Drive cannot generate a standard thumbnail.

fields.name: mimeType
fields.desc: The MIME type of the thumbnail.

fields.name: image
fields.desc: The URL-safe Base64 encoded bytes of the thumbnail image. It should conform to RFC 4648 section 5.

fields.name: editable
fields.desc: Whether the file can be edited by the current user. Deprecated: use capabilities/canEdit.

fields.name: fileExtension
fields.desc: The final component of fullFileExtension with trailing text that does not appear to be part of the extension removed. This field is only populated for files with content stored in Drive; it is not populated for Google Docs or shortcut files.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this file.

fields.name: sharingUser
fields.desc: User that shared the item with the current user, if available.

fields.name: folderColorRgb
fields.desc: Folder color as an RGB hex string if the file is a folder. The list of supported colors is available in the folderColorPalette field of the About resource. If an unsupported color is specified, it will be changed to the closest color in the palette. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: owners
fields.desc: The owner(s) of this file. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: The list of properties.

fields.name: sharedWithMeDate
fields.desc: Time at which this file was shared with the user (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp).

fields.name: ownerNames
fields.desc: Name(s) of the owner(s) of this file. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: thumbnailLink
fields.desc: A short-lived link to the file's thumbnail. Typically lasts on the order of hours. Only populated when the requesting app can access the file's content.

fields.name: fileSize
fields.desc: The size of the file in bytes. This field is only populated for files with content stored in Drive; it is not populated for Google Docs or shortcut files.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The type of file. This is always drive#file.

fields.name: markedViewedByMeDate
fields.desc: Deprecated.

fields.name: permissions
fields.desc: The list of permissions for users with access to this file. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: writersCanShare
fields.desc: Whether writers can share the document with other users. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the file.

fields.name: ownedByMe
fields.desc: Whether the file is owned by the current user. Not populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: The title of this file. Note that for immutable items such as the top level folders of Team Drives, My Drive root folder, and Application Data folder the title is constant.

fields.name: userPermission
fields.desc: The permissions for the authenticated user on this file.

fields.name: canReadRevisions
fields.desc: Whether the current user has read access to the Revisions resource of the file. Deprecated: use capabilities/canReadRevisions.

fields.name: explicitlyTrashed
fields.desc: Whether this file has been explicitly trashed, as opposed to recursively trashed.

fields.name: hasAugmentedPermissions
fields.desc: Whether any users are granted file access directly on this file. This field is only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: md5Checksum
fields.desc: An MD5 checksum for the content of this file. This field is only populated for files with content stored in Drive; it is not populated for Google Docs or shortcut files.

fields.name: trashedDate
fields.desc: The time that the item was trashed (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp). Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: defaultOpenWithLink
fields.desc: A link to open this file with the user's default app for this file. Only populated when the drive.apps.readonly scope is used.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the file.

fields.name: quotaBytesUsed
fields.desc: The number of quota bytes used by this file.

fields.name: thumbnailVersion
fields.desc: The thumbnail version for use in thumbnail cache invalidation.

fields.name: parents
fields.desc:
Collection of parent folders which contain this file.
Setting this field will put the file in all of the provided folders. On insert, if no folders are provided, the file will be placed in the default root folder.

fields.name: capabilities
fields.desc: Capabilities the current user has on the file. Each capability corresponds to a fine-grained action that a user may take.

fields.name: canCopy
fields.desc: Whether the file can be copied by the current user. For a Team Drive item, whether non-folder descendants of this item, or this item itself if it is not a folder, can be copied.

fields.name: canReadRevisions
fields.desc: Whether the current user has read access to the Revisions resource of the file. For a Team Drive item, whether revisions of non-folder descendants of this item, or this item itself if it is not a folder, can be read.

fields.name: canShare
fields.desc: Whether the file's sharing settings can be modified by the current user.

fields.name: canComment
fields.desc: Whether the current user can comment on the file.

fields.name: canEdit
fields.desc: Whether the file can be edited by the current user.

fields.name: canReadTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether the current user has read access to the Team Drive to which this file belongs. Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: canDownload
fields.desc: Whether the file can be downloaded by the current user.

fields.name: canMoveTeamDriveItem
fields.desc: Whether the current user can move this Team Drive item by changing its parent. Note that a request to change the parent for this item may still fail depending on the new parent that is being added. Only populated for Team Drive files.

fields.name: canTrash
fields.desc: Whether the file can be trashed by the current user.

fields.name: canAddChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can add children to this folder. This is always false when the item is not a folder.

fields.name: canDelete
fields.desc: Whether the file can be deleted by the current user.

fields.name: canListChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can list the children of this folder. This is always false when the item is not a folder.

fields.name: canMoveItemIntoTeamDrive
fields.desc: Whether the current user can move this item into a Team Drive. If the item is in a Team Drive, this field is equivalent to canMoveTeamDriveItem.

fields.name: canRemoveChildren
fields.desc: Whether the current user can remove children from this folder. This is always false when the item is not a folder.

fields.name: canRename
fields.desc: Whether the file can be renamed by the current user.

fields.name: canUntrash
fields.desc: Whether the file can be restored from the trash by the current user.

fields.name: exportLinks
fields.desc: Links for exporting Google Docs to specific formats.

fields.name: isAppAuthorized
fields.desc: Whether the file was created or opened by the requesting app.

fields.name: mimeType
fields.desc: The MIME type of the file. This is only mutable on update when uploading new content. This field can be left blank, and the mimetype will be determined from the uploaded content's MIME type.

fields.name: originalFilename
fields.desc: The original filename of the uploaded content if available, or else the original value of the title field. This is only available for files with binary content in Drive.

fields.name: createdDate
fields.desc: Create time for this file (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp).

fields.name: shareable
fields.desc: Whether the file's sharing settings can be modified by the current user. Deprecated: use capabilities/canShare.

fields.name: openWithLinks
fields.desc: A map of the id of each of the user's apps to a link to open this file with that app. Only populated when the drive.apps.readonly scope is used.

fields.name: fullFileExtension
fields.desc: The full file extension; extracted from the title. May contain multiple concatenated extensions, such as "tar.gz". Removing an extension from the title does not clear this field; however, changing the extension on the title does update this field. This field is only populated for files with content stored in Drive; it is not populated for Google Docs or shortcut files.

fields.name: indexableText
fields.desc: Indexable text attributes for the file (can only be written)

fields.name: text
fields.desc: The text to be indexed for this file.

fields.name: labels
fields.desc: A group of labels for the file.

fields.name: trashed
fields.desc: Whether this file has been trashed. This label applies to all users accessing the file; however, only owners are allowed to see and untrash files.

fields.name: viewed
fields.desc: Whether this file has been viewed by this user.

fields.name: hidden
fields.desc: Deprecated.

fields.name: modified
fields.desc: Whether the file has been modified by this user.

fields.name: restricted
fields.desc: Whether viewers and commenters are prevented from downloading, printing, and copying this file.

fields.name: starred
fields.desc: Whether this file is starred by the user.

fields.name: lastModifyingUserName
fields.desc: Name of the last user to modify this file.

fields.name: modifiedDate
fields.desc: Last time this file was modified by anyone (formatted RFC 3339 timestamp). This is only mutable on update when the setModifiedDate parameter is set.

schemas.name: PermissionList
schemas.desc: A list of permissions associated with a file.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: The ETag of the list.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of permissions.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#permissionList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of permissions. This field will be absent if the end of the permissions list has been reached. If the token is rejected for any reason, it should be discarded, and pagination should be restarted from the first page of results.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this list.

schemas.name: TeamDriveList
schemas.desc: A list of Team Drives.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#teamDriveList

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The page token for the next page of Team Drives.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of Team Drives.

schemas.name: CommentReply
schemas.desc: A comment on a file in Google Drive.

fields.name: modifiedDate
fields.desc: The date when this reply was last modified.

fields.name: htmlContent
fields.desc: HTML formatted content for this reply.

fields.name: content
fields.desc: The plain text content used to create this reply. This is not HTML safe and should only be used as a starting point to make edits to a reply's content. This field is required on inserts if no verb is specified (resolve/reopen).

fields.name: createdDate
fields.desc: The date when this reply was first created.

fields.name: deleted
fields.desc: Whether this reply has been deleted. If a reply has been deleted the content will be cleared and this will only represent a reply that once existed.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#commentReply.

fields.name: replyId
fields.desc: The ID of the reply.

fields.name: verb
fields.desc:
The action this reply performed to the parent comment. When creating a new reply this is the action to be perform to the parent comment. Possible values are:  
- "resolve" - To resolve a comment. 
- "reopen" - To reopen (un-resolve) a comment.

fields.name: author
fields.desc: The user who wrote this reply.

schemas.name: User
schemas.desc: Information about a Drive user.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#user.

fields.name: permissionId
fields.desc: The user's ID as visible in the permissions collection.

fields.name: picture
fields.desc: The user's profile picture.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: A URL that points to a profile picture of this user.

fields.name: displayName
fields.desc: A plain text displayable name for this user.

fields.name: emailAddress
fields.desc: The email address of the user.

fields.name: isAuthenticatedUser
fields.desc: Whether this user is the same as the authenticated user for whom the request was made.

schemas.name: ParentReference
schemas.desc: A reference to a file's parent.

fields.name: parentLink
fields.desc: A link to the parent.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: A link back to this reference.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the parent.

fields.name: isRoot
fields.desc: Whether or not the parent is the root folder.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always drive#parentReference.

schemas.name: Channel
schemas.desc: An notification channel used to watch for resource changes.

fields.name: address
fields.desc: The address where notifications are delivered for this channel.

fields.name: resourceUri
fields.desc: A version-specific identifier for the watched resource.

fields.name: params
fields.desc: Additional parameters controlling delivery channel behavior. Optional.

fields.name: payload
fields.desc: A Boolean value to indicate whether payload is wanted. Optional.

fields.name: resourceId
fields.desc: An opaque ID that identifies the resource being watched on this channel. Stable across different API versions.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: An arbitrary string delivered to the target address with each notification delivered over this channel. Optional.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of delivery mechanism used for this channel.

fields.name: expiration
fields.desc: Date and time of notification channel expiration, expressed as a Unix timestamp, in milliseconds. Optional.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: A UUID or similar unique string that identifies this channel.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies this as a notification channel used to watch for changes to a resource. Value: the fixed string "api#channel".
